# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CONSTRUDATA-360 — Environment Variables Template
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to .env.local for local development:
#   cp .env.example .env.local
#
# For production (Vercel), set these variables in the Vercel Dashboard:
#   Settings → Environment Variables
#
# NEVER commit .env, .env.local, or any file with real credentials.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Web3Forms API Key (contact form on landing page)
# Get your key at: https://web3forms.com
VITE_WEB3FORMS_KEY=your_web3forms_access_key_here

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# NOTE: Autodesk APS (Forge) credentials are NOT configured here.
# They are entered by the user at runtime via the BIM module settings modal
# and stored only in the browser's localStorage — never in code or .env files.
# For production use, consider implementing a backend proxy to avoid exposing
# the APS Client Secret in the browser.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
